cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper focuses on improving the tracking accuracy by making use of flow information in consecutive frames, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training a deep learning framework to jointly perform flow and tracking tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves feature extraction and aggregation, which are common techniques in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
